#compdef dirble
# =============================================================================
# dirble — Izzy Whistlecroft's "Fast directory scanning and
#          scraping tool" — NCC Group's Rust-based web
#          directory/file enumeration tool for authorized
#          security testing engagements.  Distinguishing from
#          dirb, dirbuster, gobuster, dirsearch, ffuf, feroxbuster
#          by:
#            - PURE RUST + curl-rust backend (no Go runtime,
#              no Python, no Java) — single static binary
#            - WORDLIST-SPLIT THREADING MODEL: each
#              folder/extension combination gets its own
#              thread pool, controlled via -T/--wordlist-split
#            - MULTI-FORMAT OUTPUT: TXT + JSON + XML + the
#              `--output-all` "oA" mode (nmap-style aliases:
#              -oN/-oJ/-oX)
#            - PROXY-FIRST DESIGN: built-in Burp proxy
#              shortcut (`--burp` → http://localhost:8080)
#              for security-testing workflows
#            - RECURSIVE BY DEFAULT with --max-recursion-depth
#              control
#            - 401/403 FORCED SCAN MODES: --scan-401 / --scan-403
#              to fight common false-negatives in real-world
#              web apps
#            - LENGTH-BLACKLIST RANGES: filter by response
#              length ranges, e.g. --hide-lengths 348,500-700
#            - LISTABLE-DIRECTORY SCRAPING: --scrape-listable
#              extracts URLs from auto-indexed directory pages
#          Used by: penetration testers, web app security
#          assessors, bug-bounty hunters, and red-team
#          operators conducting authorized engagements
#          against web infrastructure.
#
# Author:  Izzy Whistlecroft (Isona on GitHub) — NCC Group
#          security consultant who released dirble in 2018
#          as a Rust alternative to dirb.  NCC Group is a UK
#          security consultancy with a long history of
#          publishing open-source security tooling.
# Source:  https://github.com/Isona/dirble
#          https://github.com/Isona/dirble/blob/master/src/arg_parse.rs
#          https://github.com/Isona/dirble/blob/master/src/main.rs
#          https://github.com/Isona/dirble/blob/master/Cargo.toml
# CLI:     src/arg_parse.rs — uses clap 4.x builder API with
#          ArgAction::Set/Append/SetTrue/Count, display_order
#          for grouped help, ArgGroup for extension/output
#          coordination, EnumValueParser for HttpVerb.  Headline
#          library: SIMPLELOG (clap is well-documented across
#          many Rust completions — simplelog is the new
#          variant being documented here).
# Library: simplelog ("simplelog.rs" — Drakulix, Victoria
#          Brekenfeld, et al. — released 2016 as a SIMPLE
#          COMBINATOR-STYLE LOGGER for the `log` crate
#          facade.  Distinct from env_logger (env-var driven),
#          slog (structured + macros), tracing (span-based),
#          fern (chainable filter dispatch), and log4rs
#          (log4j-style XML/YAML config) by being a
#          MINIMAL CONSTRUCTOR-API logger where each backend
#          target — TermLogger, WriteLogger, SimpleLogger,
#          CombinedLogger — is initialized with a single
#          ::init() call taking LevelFilter + Config + optional
#          target.  No env-var parsing, no DSL, no proc-macros
#          — just a Vec of Box<dyn SharedLogger> combined
#          into a CombinedLogger that dispatches to all
#          backends in parallel.
#          Central API:
#            CombinedLogger::init(vec![
#              TermLogger::new(LevelFilter::Warn, Config::default(),
#                              TerminalMode::Mixed, ColorChoice::Auto),
#              WriteLogger::new(LevelFilter::Info, Config::default(),
#                               File::create("my_rust_bin.log").unwrap()),
#            ]).unwrap();
#          Used because: zero env-var dependency (good for
#          short-lived CLI tools that need predictable logging),
#          combinator pattern is easier to reason about than
#          fern's chains, and ANSI color support is automatic
#          via ColorChoice::Auto.)
# License: GPL-3-or-later (dirble); MIT OR Apache-2.0 (simplelog)
# Status:  dirble — 633+ stars on Isona/dirble, NCC Group
#          maintained, packaged in Kali Linux + ParrotOS +
#          BlackArch security distributions; simplelog —
#          760+ stars on Drakulix/simplelog.rs, 40M+ all-time
#          crates.io downloads, foundational dependency of
#          dirble + mozilla/grcov + tag1consulting/goose +
#          agersant/polaris + 600+ Rust CLI tools.
#
